javadoc:
Structured Dynamic Data type.
 
 Dynamic Structure that is built by adding data types to it.
 
 NOTE: This is a special Dynamic data-type which can only appear as a component
 created by a Dynamic data-type

methods.name: <init>
add
methods.comment: Add a component data type onto the end of the dynamic structure

params.name: componentName
params.comment: name of the field in the dynamic structure

methods.name: setComponents
methods.comment:
Set the components of the dynamic structure all at once.
 This does not add the components in, it replaces any existing ones.

params.name: componentNames
params.comment: list of field names of each component

params.name: componentDescs
params.comment: list of descriptions of each component
